      <div xml:id="bplext-d1e60" type="decretales-l1t1">
        <head xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Hd1e101">Titulus 1</head>
        <div xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Dd1e103" type="decretales-l1t1c1">
          <head xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Hd1e105">Caput 1</head>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e107"><!-- opening divisio capituli --></p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e110"><!-- Casus --></p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e113">
            <lb ed="#R"/> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e117" source="http://scta.info/resource/cice-l1t1-d1e119@8-8">Firmiter</quote> Hoc ideo dicit, quia ordo fidei nostrae probari non potest: &amp; 
            <cb ed="#R" n="b"/><!-- 8 -->
            <lb ed="#R"/>quia ubi ratio deficit, fides supplet. <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e125" target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d4-Dd1e1228">de consecratione distinctione 4 capitulo nihil est aliud</ref> &amp; <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e129" target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d5-d1e693">distinctione 
            <lb ed="#R"/>ultima capitulo ultimo</ref> arg. ut quod sermo sonat, affectus sentiat id est fides <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e134" target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d2-Dd1e1123">de consecratione distinctione 
            <lb ed="#R"/>2 capitulo revera in fine</ref> quia fides est de re non uisa <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e139" target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p2c33q3d4-d1e227">de paenitentia distinctione 4 in domo in fine.</ref>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e143">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc>  <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e149" source="http://scta.info/resource/cice-l1t1-d1e119@9-9">Credimus</quote> Hoc ideo dicit: quia dubius in fide, infidelis est infra <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e152">de 
            <lb ed="#R"/>haereticis capitulo 1</ref> et <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e157">arg. 22. q. 1. omne quod. in fine</ref>  Et est simile de accusato con<lb ed="#R"/>tra 
            quem nihil est pro<lb ed="#R"/>batum 
            &amp; sic remanet du<lb ed="#R"/>bius 
            quando se non purgat. 
            <lb ed="#R"/>Et quia fides est exor<lb ed="#R"/>dium 
            nostrae reparatio<lb ed="#R"/>nis: 
            ideo prius de ea praemittit, 
            quia prius homo 
            <lb ed="#R"/>debet instrui in fide de 
            <lb ed="#R"/>consecratione distinctione 4. ante ba<lb ed="#R"/>ptismum 
            &amp; <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e179">capitulo ante 20</ref>.
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e183">
            <!-- italic glos. seq. dat tria imilia, & submittit genus; this is almost like editorial help navigating the gloss?? -->
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e188">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e194" source="http://scta.info/resource/cice-l1t1-d1e119@11-11">Simpliciter</quote> Fides 
            <lb ed="#R"/>enim simplicibus verbis 
            <lb ed="#R"/>est proponenda 23 dist.
            <lb ed="#R"/>qui episcopus &amp; 24 distin. 
            <lb ed="#R"/>quando. Sic &amp; testimonium 
            <lb ed="#R"/>debet esse purum. 3. quaestione 9
            <lb ed="#R"/>pura. &amp; simplex debet 
            <lb ed="#R"/>esse constitutio, simili<lb ed="#R"/>ter 
            &amp; lex 4 dist. erit 
            <lb ed="#R"/>autem. Sic &amp; quaelibet 
            <lb ed="#R"/>scriptura si obscure lo<lb ed="#R"/>quatur, 
            pro non scriptu<lb ed="#R"/>ra 
            habetur ff. de iis quae pro non scri. ha. l. 1. sic &amp; testimonium obscurum 
            <lb ed="#R"/>non valet infra de prob. in praesentia. &amp; infra de test. cum clamor. &amp; ff. de in<lb ed="#R"/>ter. 
            ac. de aetetate § nihil interest. Et generaliter numquam per extranea 
            <lb ed="#R"/>verba res est proponenda, sed per vsitata. arg. 37 dist. relatum. Ioannes Andreas.
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e230">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e236">Vnus</quote> hoc dictum fuit ad differentiam plurium planetarum, quos 
            <lb ed="#R"/>quidam colebant tamquam Deos.
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e241">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e247">Verus</quote>dictus est ad differentiam fictorum.
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e250">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e256">Aeternus</quote> hoc ideo dicit, quia a misericordiae Dei nec mensuras pos<lb ed="#R"/>summus 
            ponere, nec tempora definire. <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e260">de poenitentia distinctione 1 multiplex</ref> &amp; <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e262">26 quaestione 6 is qui</ref>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e265">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e271">Immensus</quote> Id est, sine mensura: vnde dicitur: Intra omnia non 
            inclusus, extra omnia non exclusus, supra omnia non elatus. 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e275">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e281">Incommutabilis</quote> 22. quaestio 4 incommutabilis. &amp; tamen dat cuncta mo<lb ed="#R"/>ueri 
            vnde <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e285">Boethius 3 de consolatione</ref> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e287" source="http://scta.info/resource/hy7y6y-d1e67-d1e553@16-20">Stabilisque manens dat cuncta moueri</quote>, &amp;c.  
            <lb ed="#R"/>Saepe tamen mutat sententiam suam, vt ibi dicitur &amp; <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e293">c. unusquisque, in fi.</ref> 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e296">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc>  <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e302">Incomprehensibilis</quote> vnde in veteri lege dicitur. Bestia quae mon<lb ed="#R"/>tem 
            tetigerit, lapidabitur. Et illud: Accedet homo ad cor altum &amp; exalta<lb ed="#R"/>bitur 
            Deus ab eo.  Et illud: <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e308" source="http://scta.info/resource/rom11_33@1-16">O altitudo diuitiarum sapientiae et scientiae Dei, 
            <lb ed="#R"/>quam incomprehensibilia sunt opera <!-- margin has "iudicia" --> eius, &amp; inuestigabiles viae eius.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e316">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e322">Omnipotens</quote> quia omnia <sic>potest</sic> quae decent eius potentiam, &amp; quae posse 
            <lb ed="#R"/>est aliquid posse. vnde <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e328" source="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p2c33q3d2-d1e468@63-79">peccare non potest: quia peccare non est aliquid posse: 
            <lb ed="#R"/>vt ait <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e332" target="http://scta.info/resource/adt-l15-d1e1855@190-212"><name xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Nd1e333">Augustinus</name></ref> immo est aliquid non posse</quote>. vt <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e337">de poenitentia distinctione 2, capitulo ultimo § caritas</ref>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e340">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e346">Ineffabilis</quote> vnde illud: Sapientiam eius quis enarrabit? quasi dicat, nullus
          </p>
          <!-- editorial note -->
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e351">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e357">Simplex omnino</quote>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Dd1e361" type="decretales-l1t1c2">
          <head xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Hd1e363">Caput 2</head>
          <!-- division of chapter -->
          <!-- followed by casus -->
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e369">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e375">Non est generans</quote> adiectiue tenetur, id est non generat, licet sit per<lb ed="#R"/>sona 
            generans
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e380">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e386">asserit</quote> scilicet Ioachim 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e390">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e396">asserit</quote> scilicet Petrus
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e399">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e405">Qui plantat</quote> scilicet praedicando 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e408">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e414">Et qui rigat</quote> Baptizando in epistola ad Corinthios 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bplext-d1e60-d1e417">
            <lb ed="#R"/><pc type="pilcrow">¶</pc> <quote xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Qd1e423">Vnum corpus &amp;c</quote> Vnione charitatis &amp; spiritus <ref xml:id="bplext-d1e60-Rd1e425" target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d4-d1e1999">de consecratione di<lb ed="#R"/>stinctione 
            4 quaeris a me</ref> 
          </p>
          
        </div>
      </div>
